          let <m>G = {\mathbb R}^{\ast} \times {\mathbb Z}</m>.
          Define a binary operation <m>\circ</m> on <m>G</m> by <m>(a,m) \circ (b,n) = (ab,
          m + n)</m>.
          Show that <m>G</m> is a group under this operation.
      </p>
    </statement>
  </exercise>

